@hustodemon so... After reviewing the tests (didn't notice we have them for this), I realized you added that... maybe for future Windows support:
    public void testValidateBootstrapInputUserBackslash() {
        String json = "{user: 'domain\\\\admin', host: 'host.domain.com'}";
        BootstrapHostsJson input = MinionsAPI.GSON.fromJson(json, BootstrapHostsJson.class);
        List<String> validationErrors = InputValidator.INSTANCE.validateBootstrapInput(input);
        assertTrue(validationErrors.isEmpty());
    }

But that explains the backslash, not the slash. Any idea if that's used at Windows as well? I'd say it is not. We where not even testing it.

